title: #15 Notre Dame rights the ship against Navy
text:
#15 Notre Dame rights the ship against Navy Posted: Follow @AdamS_FOX28 
Notre Dame responded to their loss at Clemson the way Irish fans hoped; with a convincing win over Navy. 
The 15th ranked Fighting Irish (5-1) beat the Midshipmen (4-1) 41-24 thanks to a strong second half performance from RB C.J. Prosise and the Notre Dame defense. 
"We're excited about the victory against a very good Navy football team," said Notre Dame head coach Brian Kelly. "They challenge you for four quarters, their scheme, their players, their coaches, they make you work for everything. It's a difficult team to play." 
Prosise finished the game with 129 yards rushing and three touchdowns. The Notre Dame senior added 56 receiving yards. 
“I don’t ever want only one guy to tackle me," said Prosise, Notre Dame senior RB. "I hate it when just one guy tackles me. I always want to make it to three or four guys trying to make the tackle.” 
The Fighting Irish surrendered 21 points in the first half to Navy, but only allowed the Midshipmen to score three points on a field goal in the second half.“I think that every game we are trying to improve on something different and trying to put a complete defense together," said Notre Dame defensive lineman Isaac Rochelle. "We are trying to piece everything together to form a complete defense.” 
Notre Dame will play #17 USC next Saturday in South Bend.
